MILLION (PHOENIX) _ Gylene Hoyle's eyes were closed when she made
her $1 million. Arizona Diamondbacks second baseman Jay Bell had
nearly fouled out on pop-ups on two previous pitches. And Hoyle,
who saw her chance slipping away, couldn't bear to watch. But on
the next pitch came Bell's game-winning grand slam in the bottom of
the sixth inning against Oakland pitcher Jimmy Haynes. Hoyle, a
31-year old Chandler, Ariz., resident, had won $1 million in a
grand-slam promotion sponsored by Shamrock Farms. By AL TOBY. Story
