</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Gross me out the door!
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Yuck! What can you do with an old, moldy shoe? What do
the insides of a roach look like? Where does mucus come from? You
can learn the answers to all these scientific, yet gross, questions
at ``the yuckiest site on the Internet.'' The site, www.yucky.com,
offers many yucky experiments and projects for kids. You'll learn
how to
</P>
<P>
   preserve spider webs and how to turn a grape into a raisin in
your underwear drawer.
</P>
<P>
   Show me the money
</P>
<P>
   In 1980, my brother and I got $5 each a week for making our beds
and helping with the dishes. We want to know what the going rate
for allowance is now. Call us at 404-222-1887 or e-mail us at
nfk(at)ajc.com and tell us how much you get paid and what you have
to do for it. Be sure to tell us your name, age and phone number,
and we may use you in a story. The deadline is July 19.
</P>
<P>
   He makes us laugh
</P>
<P>
   We've seen him go back to kindergarten, play golf with Bob
Barker, become a football star and be a big daddy.
</P>
<P>
   Now you can read about his real life in the book ``Adam Sandler:
Not Too Shabby'' by Jon Salem (Scholastic, $4.99). The 85-page book
chronicles ``the life and wacky times of America's favorite movie
goofball.'' Plus, you can ogle eight pages of photos.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
