A6772 &Cx1f; tad-z
r v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-CARIBBEAN-ADVISORY13-     07-12 0263
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CARIBBEAN-ADVISORY13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MIKE WILLIAMS NAMED COX NEWSPAPERS CARIBBEAN-LATIN AMERICA
CORRESPONDENT
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Mike Williams, a reporter for the Atlanta Journal
and Constitution, will join the foreign staff of Cox Newspapers as
the chain's Caribbean-Latin America correspondent.
</P>
<P>
   Williams replaces Shelley Emling, who is relocating to London
with her husband, who will head the Fox News bureau there.
</P>
<P>
   For the past decade with the Atlanta Journal and Constitution,
Williams has been based in Florida, where he has covered everything
from airline crashes to hurricanes. During that time he has written
news features on topics ranging from the plight of migrant farm
workers to Colombian drug wars.
</P>
<P>
   He will continue to be based in Florida, but will roam the
Caribbean and Latin America in his new job.
</P>
<P>
   A native of Alabama, Williams graduated magna cum laude from
Amherst College in 1978. He began his newspaper career as a
reporter for The Independent in Robertsdale, Ala., before moving on
to reporting assignments with the Montgomery Advertiser and the
Birmingham News.
</P>
<P>
   He was a reporter with the Miami Herald from late 1985 to
mid-1989 when he joined the Atlanta newspapers. He will begin his
new assignment around Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
   Williams, 44, is married and resides in Cocoa Beach, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Cox Newspapers also has foreign correspondents based in Mexico
City, London, Moscow, Beijing, and the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
