<HEADLINE>
JOHN TRAVOLTA'S DECENT IN `CIVIL ACTION' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``A Civil Action'' _ Local interest should make
this adaptation of Jonathan Harr's book about corporate coverup a
big renter. John Travolta is decent in the main role, but he
doesn't give the dogged lawyer enough dimension. Robert Duvall is
an understated marvel as the attorney pitted against the star. It's
no contest. Also, they should have shot more scenes in the Route
128-Woburn area to give it more authenticity. Also on DVD.
</P>
<P>
   ``Central Station'' _ Fernanda Montenegro gave the best
performance of any of the 1998 Oscar-nominated actresses as Dora, a
cynical clerk who gradually comes to appreciate life through the
intercession of a young boy. Walter Salles's film could have become
a maudlin mess if it were not for Montenegro's low-key brilliance.
If justice and good judgment prevailed, she would have an Academy
Award on her mantelpiece.
</P>
<P>
   ``Waco: The Rules of Engagement'' _ This hard-hitting
documentary paints a very unpleasant picture of law enforcement _
particularly, the FBI. Basically, it tries to answer the question _
why did so many Branch Davidians die in the infamous engagement?
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING VHS ATTRACTIONS: July 20: ``8MM,'' ``The General,''
``Down in the Delta,'' ``Virus,'' ``Mercenary 2,'' ``Double
Platinum,'' ``Resurrection Man.'' July 27: ``Baby Geniuses,''
``October Sky,'' Naked City.'' Aug. 3: ``A Midsummer Night's
Dream,'' ``Tango,'' ``Cruel Intentions,'' ``Message in a Bottle,''
``Runnin' Wild: The Films of Clara Bow.'' Aug. 10: ``Shakespeare in
Love,'' ``True Crime,'' ``The Mod Squad,'' ``Lock, Stock and Two
Smoking Barrels,'' ``Unmade Beds,'' ``The Deep End of the Ocean,''
``Celebrity.'' '' Aug. 17: ``Analyze This,'' ``200 Cigarettes.''
Aug. 24: ``Go,'' ``Chameleon.'' Aug. 31: ``Cleopatra.'' Sept. 7:
``The Other Sister.'' &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS ON DVD: July 20-30: ``8MM,'' ``Always,''
``Baby Geniuses,'' ``Blast from the Past,'' ``Cool Runnings,''
``Down in the Delta,'' ``Dream Lover,'' ``The General,'' ``I Love
Trouble,'' ``Little Buddha,'' ``Mallrats,'' ``Mr. Holland's Opus,''
``October Sky,'' ``Pallbearer,'' ``Payback,'' ``Restoration,''
``Romy and Michele's High School Reunion,'' ``Smoke Signals,''
``The Trigger Effect,'' ``Virus,'' ``What's Love Got to Do with
It?.'' Aug. 31: ``Titanic.''
</P>
</TEXT>
