<P>
   NATION
</P>
<P>
   BLACKWHITE-ADOPTION _ The Florida Department of Children and
Families changes its mind, says a white mom can adopt a black
child. Under the settlement agreement, Shirley Fitzgerald gets to
adopt a black child, the black relatives have limited visitation,
and DCF has to pay $135,000 in legal fees and costs incurred by the
foster parent to fight the case. DCF, which had fought vehemently
against the bi-racial adoption, says it didn't have all the info it
needed initially to make a decision. And now that it has
psychological and other assessments of the child, it agrees that
the best place is with Shirley Fitzgerald. (McLachlin, Palm Beach
Post).
</P>
<P>
   SKOLSHOOT-DELAY _ ATLANTA _ The lawyer for Heritage High School
(Rockdale County, Ga.) shooting suspect Anthony ``T.J.'' Solomon
has won a delay to give Solomon's lawyers more time to prepare
their case. (Stafford, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
