<SLUG> BC-COOLMUSICIANS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAKING A CASE FOR OTHER INSTRUMENTS
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies COOL CLARINETIST) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By WAYNE LEE GAY 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Even though the piano, violin and cello _ and in recent years,
the guitar _ get all the good breaks and solo engagements, every
generation produces a few stars who manage to find or make a niche
for other instruments. Here are some artists who have made a spot
for themselves in spite of the odds.
</P>
<P>
   PERCUSSION: British percussionist Evelyn Glennie, who is
profoundly deaf, has established herself as one of the most
captivating performers and great musical geniuses of our time.
</P>
<P>
   VIOLA: Russian Yuri Bashmet has moved boldly into the vacant
slot for a solo violist. Vlinist Pinchas Zukerman occasionally
shows off by picking up the viola.
</P>
<P>
   DOUBLE BASS: Canny marketing as well as crossover hits _ and
superb playing _ have allowed Gary Karr and Edgar Meyer, each in
his own way, to become well-known on the largest and lowest-pitched
member of the string family.
</P>
<P>
   FLUTE: The dual reign of Jean-Pierre Rampal and the incredibly
personable James Galway (who began his career as an orchestral
musician) continues, with Paula Robison, Eugenia Zukerman (Pinchas
Zukerman's ex-wife) and Ransom Wilson providing a notable tier of
heirs apparent.
</P>
<P>
   TRUMPET: Wynton Marsalis continues his reign as all-around
musical genius, while Swedish trumpeter Hakan Hardenberger has
become prominent as a traditional concert artist.
</P>
<P>
   CLARINET: American Richard Stolzman holds the niche as the one
well-known audience favorite in America.
</P>
<P>
   OBOE: Swiss oboist Heinz Holliger started out as an orchestral
player and built his solo career around a combination of early and
modern solo music.
</P>
<P>
   OTHERS: Surprisingly, the horn slot remains vacant and waiting
for a new star since the retirement of Barry Tuckwell, while the
bassoon, harp, trombone and tuba still await the right combination
of personality and artistry to capture the public imagination.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
