<P>
   GRAM PARSONS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The late Gram Parsons practically invented what has
come to be known as alternative-country: Wilco, Son Volt,
Whiskeytown, Golden Smog _ and the Eagles and the Rolling Stones'
``Wild Horses,'' too _ probably wouldn't have existed without
Parsons' trailblazing work. On Tuesday, some of the debt will be
repaid with the release of ``Return of the Grievous Angel: A
Tribute to Gram Parsons,'' a 13-song valentine that shows just how
far his shadow reached. By DAVE FERMAN. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COOL CLARINETIST &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Swedish clarinetist Martin Frost is a renowned touring
soloist in Europe and Japan, where he makes his living playing with
orchestras and in recitals. But in America, Frost is almost
unknown. When Frost performs with the Mimir Chamber Music Festival
at Texas Christian University in Fort Worth this week, it will be
his second visit to the United States. His first performance in
this country came during the same festival last year. So why has he
been so slow to catch on here? By WAYNE LEE GAY. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. (Accompanied by COOL MUSICIANS.) &QL; 
