<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Did anybody catch the irony in President Clinton's
suggestion that George W. Bush is ``hostile'' to campaign finance
reform because he might decline federal funding for his
presidential race? For this money-grubbing slimeball of a president
to raise questions about any candidate's commitment to campaign
finance reform is the height of hypocrisy. By BILL THOMPSON. Story
has moved in ``k'' commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SMITH-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Young people are still starting to smoke, partly
because it's a ``cool'' thing to do. And once they start, it's hard
to stop. The American Lung Association estimates that, of the 47
million Americans who smoke, 31 million would like to stop. But the
good news is that an estimated 44 million adults are ex-smokers.
Now, that's cool. By JACK Z. SMITH. Story has moved in ``k''
commentary category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
