<P>
   Anyone trying to cast a play or plan a social event has come
face-to-face with what scientists call a satisfiability problem.
Suppose that a theatrical director feels obligated to cast either
his ingenue, Actress Alvarez, or his nephew, Actor Cohen, in a
production. But Miss Alvarez won't be in a play with Cohen (her
former lover), VVKQ!QQ! MQ%9 1U!I9]15 Q &QC; IY9A &QC; IQQ!AI &QC; U
