<P>
   CHINA-TAIWAN (Beijing) _ Taiwan has abandoned the political
formula that has long kept the peace with China, declaring that it
will no longer adhere to the line that the Chinese mainland and
Taiwan are two parts of the same country. Beijing's response is
immediate, and furious. Breaking with the ``one-China'' stance that
has been a basic condition of all its talks with Beijing, Taiwan's
president, Lee Teng-hui, has chosen to take a step away from the
conceptual umbrella of eventual reunification between China and
Taiwan. By Seth Faison. 1,500 words.
</P>
