<SLUG> BC-LADN-SPORTS-BUDGET- </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
July 13 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Joe Jares at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
GLF-CROUSE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Although the British Open is a
major tournament, it isn't to five Americans. 
By Karen Crouse. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODANAL (Los Angeles) _ Analysis of the Los Angeles Dodgers'
first half. w/report card. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
SOC-FUTURE (Pasadena, Calif.) _ Despite the enormous success of the
Women's World Cup, don't expect a women's pro soccer league to work
on the same level as other pro leagues in this country. 
By Jim Barrero/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.) 
 
 
