   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS-HISPANICS (Houston) _ Telemundo chairman and chief
executive Roland Hernandez issues a letter a apology to Houston
Astros owner Drayton McLane Jr. after an executive of the
Spanish-language television station KTMD accused McLane of making
insensitive remarks about Hispanics. By JOHN WILLIAMS. (Already
filed.)
</P>
<P>
   BBO-ALL-STAR (Boston) _ In this era where 12-11 slugfests are
becoming almost routine, Boston's Pedro Martinez is on a pace to
become the first pitcher to win 30 games in more than 30 years. And
Martinez, who carries a 15-3 record into his All-Star starting
assignment Tuesday night, is doing it at Fenway Park, of all
places. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Boston) _ For first-time All-Stars Billy Wagner,
Mike Hampton and Jose Lima of the Houston Astros, this is a pretty
special day. Just being in Boston for the 1999 All-Star Game. Just
getting to play at Fenway Park. And just being in the clubhouse
with the Barry Bonds and Ken Griffeys of the world. By JOSEPH
DUARTE.
</P>
