<DOCNO> NYT19990712.0376 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-12 21:07 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7442 &Cx1f; taf-z
u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-EXP-CLINTON-GOP-NYT &LR;      07-12 0397
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EXP-CLINTON-GOP-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CLINTON MEETS WITH GOP LEADERS ON TAX ISSUES 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 By JOHN M. BRODER   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Talks began in earnest in the Oval Office late
Monday afternoon on matters of social policy and money that will
drive negotiations in Washington through the fall budget-writing
season, and probably well into the 2000 campaign.
</P>
<P>
   President Clinton invited Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott,
House Speaker Dennis Hastert and House Majority Leader Dick Armey
to the White House to discuss his plans for Medicare and Social
Security and to hear Republican proposals for large tax cuts. The
Democratic leaders of the Senate and House, Tom Daschle and Dick
Gephardt, also attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
   The president told the Republican leaders that he is willing to
