that a generation of young doctors dazzled by LED displays and
computer printouts is turning away from the hands-on skills that,
once forgotten, may never be retrieved. ``If you have available
technology as an alternative, you're going to rust at the
bedside,'' says Mangione. (Sal DiMarco, Jr./New York Times Photo)
