<P>
   (NYT3) NORTHBOROUGH, Mass. -- July12, 1999 --
BBO-ALLST-FIDRYCH-BOS, 07-12 -- Mark Fidrych relaxes with his dog,
Patches, at his home in Northborough. In 1976, Fidrych had a
magical year in baseball, moving from the minors to the majors and
pitching at the All-Star game. (Dominic Chavez/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) BOSTON -- July12, 1999 -- SCI-HEALTH-BOS, 07-12 -- A lot
more research is needed to determine how to maximize different
nutrients, says Dr. Jeffrey Blumberg, a professor of nutrition at
Tufts University. He says scientists have only focused on
phytochemicals, or plant compounds, for the last 10 years and have
just started to see results in the last five. (Wendy Maeda/Boston
Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) CAMBRIDGE, Mass. -- July12, 1999 -- PROFILE-GARDNER-BOS,
07-12 --Dr. Howard Gardner, a Harvard University psychologist and
educator. Gardner, 56, has added five intelligences to the
traditional pair of linguistic and logical/mathematic: musical,
spatial, interpersonal, intrapersonal, and bodily-kinesthetic. He
has recently added naturalist, and is considering a ninth,
existential. (Tom Herde/Boston Globe Photo)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
