<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: LIKE WOODSTOCK, BEADS RETURN 
</HEADLINE>
  (lh) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ All manner of beaded jewelry has taken off this
summer, from Stella Pace's prayer-bead-inspired elastic bracelets
to Indian beadwork chokers to Kazuko's refined necklaces on gold
wire.
</P>
<P>
   The Stella Pace bracelets, which caught on last year in
hematite, are available in many semiprecious stones, for less than
$30 just about everywhere. Kazuko's neck rings, each with a single
stone, are $200 to $225 at Barneys New York. Colorful Huichol
Indian bracelets are $85 to $120 at Saks Fifth Avenue, and chokers
are $198 at Henri Bendel.
</P>
<P>
   Bendel's also has bracelets of caviar-size beads by How Charming
at $58 for a set of 15 strands. Miriam Haskell's versions of these
with crystals and freshwater pearls are $85 at Saks. Miriam Salat's
multistrand bracelets with silver toggles are $100 in solid colors,
$135 with multicolored beads, at Neiman Marcus. Necklaces of
turquoise or coral by Erickson Beamon are $135 to $495 at Barneys.
</P>
</TEXT>
