<HEADLINE>
CHIEF OF CIRCULATION NAMED BY THE TIMES 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Scott H. Heekin-Canedy, vice president for strategic
planning at The New York Times, has been appointed the newspaper's
senior vice president for circulation. He succeeds Richard H.
Gilman, who was named by the parent Times Co. on Monday to be
publisher of The Boston Globe. Heekin-Canedy's appointment was
announced by Janet L. Robinson, president and general manager of
The Times.
</P>
<P>
   Heekin-Canedy, 47, has held his strategic planning post since
1997 and had been group director in that department since 1994.
</P>
<P>
   A 1974 graduate of Williams College, he has a Doctor of Laws
degree from the Northeastern University School of Law and an MBA in
marketing and finance from Columbia University. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
